    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grain threshing tools of ancient Rome consisting of a heavy wooden board or sledge with iron or stone teeth fixed to the underside that through a rubbing action released the grain from the straw, leaving the chaff to be removed in another process.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
